BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Humanities West Presents The Etruscans
DTSTART:20260530T000000Z
DTEND:20260530T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:2be2dc7f-b7ce-5d06-b3ad-f28f9acc9580
DESCRIPTION:The Etruscan culture\, which flourished from the ninth to the 
 first centuries B.C. in Tuscany\, left behind a rich history with many uni
 que traditions that are reflected in the artistic objects found in their t
 ombs\, temples\, sanctuaries and homes. Renée Dreyfus and Lisa Pieraccini
  will discuss the latest advances in scholarship and archeological discove
 ries\, and in the translation of the Etruscan language\, which have been l
 eading historians to an ever better understanding of the Etruscan contribu
 tions to Roman architecture\, art and engineering.\n\nMore info & tickets:
  https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-05-29/humanities-west-presen
 ts-etruscans
LOCATION:The Commonwealth Club of California\, 110 The Embarcadero\, San F
 rancisco\, CA
URL:https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-05-29/humanities-west-pre
 sents-etruscans
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
