DTEND:20260603T030000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:cece31a7-ab71-5046-b6b2-068a11fa74ea
DESCRIPTION:Conversation and Live Performance\nBay Area native Deke Sharon
  is widely regarded as the “father of contemporary a cappella.” As mus
 ic director for the popular Pitch Perfect film franchise and NBC’s “Th
 e Sing-Off\,” Sharon has done more than perhaps anyone to bring a cappel
 la from churches and college quads into the mainstream—helping spark a 2
 1st-century resurgence of the genre. Or in the words of a 2013 NPR headlin
 e: “Deke Sharon Makes A Cappella Cool Again”\n\nMore info & tickets: h
 ttps://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-06-02/cappella-road-trip-pitch
 -perfect-music-director-deke-sharon-and-pacific-edge
LOCATION:Commonwealth Club World Affairs of California\, Taube Family Audi
 torium\, San Francisco\, CA
URL:https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-06-02/cappella-road-trip-
 pitch-perfect-music-director-deke-sharon-and-pacific-edge
END:VEVENT
