BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ben Rhodes: All We Say\, the Battle for American Identity
DTSTART:20260612T013000Z
DTEND:20260612T033000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:56880e5a-f946-5c46-83ac-23cf97d7a313
DESCRIPTION:What does it mean to be American? Who gets to decide? \nAmeri
 cans have debated those questions for 250 years. The issue of what it mean
 s to be an American shaped the compromises in the Constitution and the arg
 uments we’ve been having ever since—spawning abolitionism\, secession\
 , and civil war\; populism\, mass migration\, and global leadership\; move
 ments for reform and the backlashes to them. \n\nMore info & tickets: htt
 ps://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-06-11/ben-rhodes-all-we-say-batt
 le-american-identity
LOCATION:Louis B. Mayer Theatre\, Santa Clara University\, Santa Clara\, C
 A
URL:https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-06-11/ben-rhodes-all-we-s
 ay-battle-american-identity
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Contested Continent: The Struggle for North America\, c. 1000–16
 80
DTSTART:20260616T000000Z
DTEND:20260616T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:24e75e0d-b0b0-5317-b9f1-a1697a40be76
DESCRIPTION:North America was forged from the experiences of millions of I
 ndigenous women and men as well as Europeans and Africans. Contested Conti
 nent\, the first volume of the Oxford History of the United States series\
 , is a far-ranging history of North America concentrating on the period fr
 om c. A.D. 1000 to 1680—from the arrival of Norse explorers to an explos
 ion of revolts that underlined the stubborn struggle to master the contine
 nt some two centuries after Columbus’s landfall.\n\nMore info & tickets:
  https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-06-15/contested-continent-st
 ruggle-north-america-c-1000-1680
LOCATION:The Commonwealth Club of California\, Toni Rembe Rock Auditorium\
 , San Francisco\, CA
URL:https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-06-15/contested-continent
 -struggle-north-america-c-1000-1680
END:VEVENT
