BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Lost Founder: James Wilson and the Forgotten Fight for a Peopl
 e’s Constitution
DTSTART:20260715T003000Z
DTEND:20260715T023000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:f8151854-9c7b-53b3-8039-1c16a94d9acd
DESCRIPTION:Founding Father James Wilson’s bold vision for American demo
 cracy was lost to scandal. As a young lawyer\, Wilson made the case for Am
 erican independence in an essay that inspired the famous words “We hold 
 these truths to be self-evident\, that all men are created equal.” He wr
 ote the first draft of the Constitution and\, along with the much more fam
 ous James Madison\, played an essential role in its creation.\n\nMore info
  & tickets: https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-07-14/lost-founde
 r-james-wilson-and-forgotten-fight-peoples-constitution
LOCATION:The Commonwealth Club of California\, Toni Rembe Rock Auditorium\
 , San Francisco\, CA
URL:https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-07-14/lost-founder-james-
 wilson-and-forgotten-fight-peoples-constitution
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Uninformed Consent: Governance in MAGA’s Post-Journalistic Ameri
 ca
DTSTART:20260722T013000Z
DTEND:20260722T033000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:f0b07d64-da27-55bc-bb2a-d0242129f59e
DESCRIPTION:In this timely presentation\, media scholar and critic Nolan H
 igdon deconstructs the sophisticated strategies of information management 
 defining Donald Trump’s second term. Higdon argues that the administrati
 on has evolved beyond simple "fake news" rhetoric into a regime of systemi
 c institutional control. He provides a granular analysis of the 2025 media
  policy shifts—specifically the mass de-credentialing of veteran journal
 ists at the Defense Department and the strategic clearing of the press poo
 l to make way for loyalist-owned alternatives.\n\nMore info & tickets: htt
 ps://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-07-21/uninformed-consent-governa
 nce-magas-post-journalistic-america
LOCATION:Lafayette Public Library\, Don Tatzin Auditorium\, Lafayette\, CA
URL:https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-07-21/uninformed-consent-
 governance-magas-post-journalistic-america
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:DJ DiDonna: The Transformative Power of Sabbaticals
DTSTART:20260724T010000Z
DTEND:20260724T030000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:abe913be-0014-593b-8bef-dd0345b53e16
DESCRIPTION:The professional world usually prioritizes urgency\, but the m
 ost important moments of our lives rarely happen at the desk. In his new b
 ook Big Time Off\, Sabbatical Project founder DJ DiDonna offers up a simpl
 e but radical idea: sabbaticals help us avoid sleepwalking through life by
  giving us time to be present in moments of celebration\, difficulty\, and
  transition.\n\nMore info & tickets: https://www.commonwealthclub.org/even
 ts/2026-07-23/dj-didonna-transformative-power-sabbaticals
LOCATION:Commonwealth Club World Affairs of California\, Taube Family Audi
 torium\, San Francisco\, CA
URL:https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-07-23/dj-didonna-transfor
 mative-power-sabbaticals
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ben Wikler: How to End America’s Meltdown and Save Democracy
DTSTART:20260729T010000Z
DTEND:20260729T030000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:f9bd0b1f-9986-5941-b93c-9e166198eeda
DESCRIPTION:Wisconsin was written off by many Democrats after the GOP gain
 ed total control over the state’s executive\, judicial\, and legislative
  branches. For a while\, the state—once known for clean government and t
 ransparency—became a national symbol of a highly gerrymandered state. Bu
 t the Democrats figured out how to win\, and they slowly and methodically 
 rebuilt their power\, regaining the governor’s office\, cutting into leg
 islative majorities\, and are now on a run of consecutive landslide electi
 on victories for Democratic-leaning state supreme court justices\, who are
  in the majority.\n\nMore info & tickets: https://www.commonwealthclub.org
 /events/2026-07-28/ben-wikler-how-end-americas-meltdown-and-save-democracy
LOCATION:Commonwealth Club World Affairs of California\, 110 The Embarcade
 ro\, San Francisco\, CA
URL:https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-07-28/ben-wikler-how-end-
 americas-meltdown-and-save-democracy
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Rashad Robinson: From Presence to Power
DTSTART:20260730T003000Z
DTEND:20260730T023000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:270c044c-a96c-56cc-b9fc-87adb7287a3a
DESCRIPTION:Why do some struggles for justice succeed while others stall? 
 What is needed to make effective social change\, especially in today’s w
 orld? According to Rashad Robinson\, it comes down to understanding the di
 fference between presence and power. Failing to do so is one reason things
  got this way\, but understanding how power really works is a big part of 
 how we get out of it.\n\nMore info & tickets: https://www.commonwealthclub
 .org/events/2026-07-29/rashad-robinson-presence-power
LOCATION:Commonwealth Club World Affairs of California\, Toni Rembe Audito
 rium\, San Francisco\, CA
URL:https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-07-29/rashad-robinson-pre
 sence-power
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tremendous Telescopes: The Future of American Space Observation
DTSTART:20260731T003000Z
DTEND:20260731T023000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:eac6d3c0-6237-5e12-a8cb-1fa71be01b9d
DESCRIPTION:For 500 years\, telescopes have opened windows on the cosmos w
 ith increasing power and precision. Beginning with the historic telescopes
  funded by Andrew Carnegie and built by George Ellery Hale atop Pasadena
 ’s Mount Wilson\, where Edwin Hubble confirmed the existence of the univ
 erse beyond our Milky Way galaxy and revealed its continual expansion\, th
 e United States has stood at the vanguard of observational technology.\n\n
 More info & tickets: https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-07-30/tr
 emendous-telescopes-future-american-space-observation
LOCATION:The Commonwealth Club of California\, Toni Rembe Rock Auditorium\
 , San Francisco\, CA
URL:https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-07-30/tremendous-telescop
 es-future-american-space-observation
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pria Anand: A Neurologist on the Strangeness and Wonders of Our Br
 ain
DTSTART:20260731T010000Z
DTEND:20260731T030000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:9a817d91-c6cf-543e-a3d1-f64a772762e0
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a talk with a neurologist as she reckons with the 
 stories we tell about our brains—and the stories our brains tell us.Such
  as: A girl believes she has been struck blind for stealing a kiss. A moth
 er watches helplessly as each of her children is replaced by a changeling.
  A woman is haunted each month by the same four chords of a single song. 
 \n\nMore info & tickets: https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-07-3
 0/pria-anand-neurologist-strangeness-and-wonders-our-brain
LOCATION:Commonwealth Club World Affairs of California\, Taube Family Audi
 torium\, San Francisco\, CA
URL:https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-07-30/pria-anand-neurolog
 ist-strangeness-and-wonders-our-brain
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ecocivilization: Making a World That Works for All
DTSTART:20260806T003000Z
DTEND:20260806T023000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:b790d89f-b5e8-59e0-b09c-f564ece67be3
DESCRIPTION:It has been said that it is easier to imagine the end of the w
 orld than it is to imagine the end of capitalism. Yet Jeremy Lent says tha
 t is what this historical moment urgently calls for. As climate chaos\, in
 equality and social fragmentation intensify\, humanity faces an imminent c
 hoice: continue with a system built on extraction and endless growth\, or 
 reimagine civilization itself. He says incremental policy improvements are
  no longer enough\, and what is needed is a deep transformation of our cur
 rent civilization to continue to survive.\n\nMore info & tickets: https://
 www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-08-05/ecocivilization-making-world-wo
 rks-all
LOCATION:The Commonwealth Club of California\, Toni Rembe Rock Auditorium\
 , San Francisco\, CA
URL:https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-08-05/ecocivilization-mak
 ing-world-works-all
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Investing in a Resilient Future: From Climate Finance to Human Hea
 lth
DTSTART:20260807T010000Z
DTEND:20260807T030000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:d0807682-b9e6-518a-a7c2-c5708869e532
DESCRIPTION:Rising temperatures and unpredictable natural and human-made e
 vents are disrupting food systems worldwide\, threatening the long-term ec
 onomic and health risks to families. Across the globe\, smallholder farmer
 s produce around one-third of the total share of the world’s food\, yet 
 are disproportionately affected by climate risks\, uncertainty\, and pover
 ty\, often having limited resources to adapt to these changes.Then how are
  these communities building resilience and developing better strategies?\n
 \nMore info & tickets: https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-08-06/
 investing-resilient-future-climate-finance-human-health
LOCATION:Commonwealth Club World Affairs of California\, 110 The Embarcade
 ro\, San Francisco\, CA
URL:https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-08-06/investing-resilient
 -future-climate-finance-human-health
END:VEVENT
