SUMMARY:Victoria Yeager: Chuck Yeager Had the Right Stuff
DTSTART:20260827T010000Z
DTEND:20260827T030000Z
DTSTAMP:20260524T214200Z
UID:1f4a0210-5a26-58f5-8efd-11a989809f56
DESCRIPTION:Join us to hear about the extraordinary life and legacy of Ame
 rican aviation hero Chuck Yeager\, presented by his widow Victoria Yeager.
  She traces Chuck’s journey from a curious\, hardworking boy who grew up
  in the hills of West Virginia to a fearless pilot who changed the course 
 of aviation history. She illustrates Yeager’s service in World War II as
  a fighter pilot\, his daring escape after being shot down over France\, h
 is rise as a decorated ace\, and his breaking the sound barrier on October
  14\, 1947\, flying faster than MACH 1\, the speed of sound\, in a Bell X-
 1. \n\nMore info & tickets: https://www.commonwealthclub.org/events/2026-
 08-26/victoria-yeager-chuck-yeager-had-right-stuff
LOCATION:The Commonwealth Club of California\, Taube Family Auditorium\, S
